@page "/Technologies"

<PageTitle>Technologies Used in SPAs</PageTitle>

<div class="main-content">
    <h1>Technologies Used in SPAs</h1>

    <h3>Document Hashes</h3>
    <p>Unique identifiers for data integrity verification.</p>

    <h3>JavaScript Frameworks</h3>
    <p>Tools for building dynamic, interactive SPAs.</p>

    <h3>AngularJS</h3>
    <p>A framework for dynamic views with two-way data binding.</p>

    <h3>Ember.js</h3>
    <p>An opinionated framework with a powerful router.</p>

    <h3>ExtJS</h3>
    <p>Offers a rich set of UI components for complex apps.</p>

    <h3>Knockout.js</h3>
    <p>Uses the MVVM pattern for responsive UI bindings.</p>

    <h3>Meteor.js</h3>
    <p>A full-stack framework with real-time sync between client and server.</p>

    <h3>React</h3>
    <p>Component-based UI library with a virtual DOM.</p>

    <h3>Vue.js</h3>
    <p>A progressive framework with reactive data binding.</p>

    <h3>Svelte</h3>
    <p>Compiles at build time for optimized runtime performance.</p>

    <h3>Data Transport (XML, JSON, Ajax)</h3>
    <p>Methods for sending data between client and server.</p>

    <h3>WebSockets</h3>
    <p>Real-time, bidirectional communication protocol.</p>

    <h3>Server-sent Events (SSE)</h3>
    <p>Server pushes updates to the client over HTTP.</p>
</div>